The article discusses the tragic milestone of 800,000 American deaths due to COVID-19 and emphasizes the importance of remembering and honoring each person's life. The author acknowledges the pain of losing loved ones, especially during the holiday season. The article highlights the efforts made over the past 11 months to combat the virus, including the successful vaccination program, which has saved over one million American lives. Currently, more than 200 million Americans are fully vaccinated, and the author encourages people to get their booster shots and take preventive measures such as masking. The vaccines are described as safe, effective, free, and easy, and are emphasized as the best tool to prevent further loss and pain. The author urges all Americans to do their patriotic duty by keeping the country safe, protecting themselves and others, and honoring the memory of those who have been lost.